{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"ida1cd6f9a-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95","identifier":"/us/usc/t32/s312"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"312"},"text":"§ 312.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Appointment oath","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Each person who is appointed as an officer of the National Guard shall subscribe to the following oath:","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“I, ______, do solemnly swear (or affirm) that I will support and defend the Constitution of the United States and the Constitution of the State of ______ against all enemies, foreign and domestic; that I will bear true faith and allegiance to the same; that I will obey the orders of the President of the United States and of the Governor of the State of ______, that I make this obligation freely, without any mental reservation or purpose of evasion, and that I will well and faithfully discharge the duties of the office of ____ in the National Guard of the State of ______ upon which I am about to enter, so help me God.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"ida1cd6f9b-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/603"},"text":"70A Stat. 603","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"ida1cd6f9c-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"ida1cd6f9d-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"ida1cd6f9e-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null